=head1 DESCRIPTION

A structure that describes the sign-in options for an application
portal.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 ApplicationUrl => Str

The URL that accepts authentication requests for an application. This
is a required parameter if the C<Origin> parameter is C<APPLICATION>.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Origin => Str

This determines how IAM Identity Center navigates the user to the
target application. It can be one of the following values:

=over

=item *

C<APPLICATION>: IAM Identity Center redirects the customer to the
configured C<ApplicationUrl>.

=item *

C<IDENTITY_CENTER>: IAM Identity Center uses SAML identity-provider
initiated authentication to sign the customer directly into a
SAML-based application.

=back




